"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720296","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-21","<p>In the light of the 19 April motion in the House of Commons agreeing to a general election to be held on 8 June, any plans for a cross-government meeting on cyber hate will need to be revisited in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-04-21T09:27:16.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720296/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720296/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720296/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-13","Cybercrime: Hate Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, on what date in June the cross-government meeting on cyber hate will be held; and with whom her Department is consulting on that subject in advance of that meeting.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","70432"
