"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720299","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-20","<p>Basic data about the number and locations of each public library in England as at 1 July 2016 was published on gov.uk on 30 March 2017.The Libraries Taskforce is currently conducting a survey until Friday 28 April seeking views from the sector on what a core dataset for public libraries in England should contain, such as information in relation to each library on the number of hours open and the number of staffed hours each week.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","70657","2017-04-20T15:25:48.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720299/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720299/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720299/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-13","Public Libraries: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to her Department's public libraries basic data set, published on 30 March 2017, what additional information she plans to include in the full data set collected by the Libraries Taskforce.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","70603"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720300","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-25","<p>On 16 March 2017, the Secretary of State made a statement to Hon. Members [Official Report - Vol 623 col 556] that she had intervened in the proposed acquisition of Sky plc by 21st Century Fox Inc on media public interest grounds and had issued a European Intervention Notice (EIN). Ofcom will consider any possible effects of 21st Century Fox Inc's bid for Sky plc on media plurality in their report on the media public interests mentioned in the EIN. Ofcom will now submit their report by 20 June 2017.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-04-25T12:19:23.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720300/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720300/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720300/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-13","21st Century Fox: Sky","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will make an assessment of the potential effect of Rupert Murdoch's bid for Sky TV on media plurality.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","70593"
